he%20Scholastic%20Book%20Fair%20came%20to%20his%20library%2C%20he'd%20beg%20his%20parents%20for%20cash%20to%20buy%20NASA%20photo%20books.%20To%20him%2C%20space%20science%20seemed%20the%20pinnacle%20of%20innovation%2C%20excitement%2C%20and%20existentialism.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%20when%2C%20as%20a%20sophomore%20in%20college%2C%20he%20told%20his%20parents%20he%20was%20going%20to%20major%20in%20accounting%2C%20they%20gave%20him%20what%20Bryan%20(which%20isn't%20his%20real%20name)%20could%20describe%20only%20as%20%26quot%3Ba%20look.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAn%20accountant%3F%26quot%3B%20he%20remembers%20his%20mother%20saying.%20%26quot%3BWhy%20would%20you%20want%20to%20be%20an%20accountant%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECertified%20public%20accountants%20have%20long%20been%20cast%20as%20penny-pinching%20list%20checkers%20with%20vanilla%20personalities%20and%20a%20zeal%20for%20taxes%2C%20but%20that%20stereotype%20seems%20to%20turn%20off%20Gen%20Z%20more%20than%20any%20previous%20generation.%20That%20perception%20plus%20the%20industry's%20actual%20hurdles%20and%20pitfalls%20have%20compounded%20in%20the%20past%20several%20years%20to%20create%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fshortage-accountants-we-should-be-worried-recruit-young-talent-2023-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Enationwide%20accountant%20shortage%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20American%20Institute%20of%20Certified%20Public%20Accountants%20says%20about%2065%2C000%20students%20in%20the%20US%20completed%20bachelor's%20or%20master's%20degrees%20in%20accounting%20in%20the%202021-22%20school%20year%2C%2018%25%20fewer%20than%20a%20decade%20earlier.%20Of%20those%20who%20study%20accounting%2C%20only%20a%20portion%20become%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-get-hired-top-consulting-firms-bcg-mckinsey-pwc-2024-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecertified%20public%20accountants%3C%2Fa%3E.%20About%2030%2C000%20people%20took%20the%20CPA%20exam%20in%202022%2C%20compared%20with%20nearly%2050%2C000%20people%20in%202010.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20longtime%20accountants'%20ranks%20are%20dwindling%20fast%3A%20Three-quarters%20of%20CPAs%20in%20the%20US%20were%20thought%20to%20be%20at%20or%20near%20retirement%20in%202019.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20hard%20to%20overstate%20the%20consequences%20of%20a%20lack%20of%20accountants.%20It's%20not%20just%20the%20neighborhood%20CPA%20taking%20longer%20than%20usual%20to%20finish%20your%20tax%20return%20%E2%80%94%20we've%20already%20started%20to%20see%20it%20can%20mean%20financial%20mistakes%20and%20discrepancies%20at%20the%20highest%20levels%20of%20corporate%20America.%20Last%20year%2C%20for%20example%2C%20Advance%20Auto%20Parts%20said%20turnover%20of%20accounting%20staff%20was%20a%20cause%20for%20%26quot%3Bmaterial%20weakness%26quot%3B%20in%20its%20financial%20reporting%20via%20a%20filing%20extension%20request%20to%20the%20Security%20and%20Exchange%20Commission.%20Container%20maker%20Tupperware%20recently%20had%20similar%20delays%20in%20filing%20because%20of%20%26quot%3Bsignificant%20attrition%26quot%3B%20and%20%26quot%3Bskill%20set%20gaps%26quot%3B%20in%20its%20accounting%20department.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccountants%20have%20become%20an%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fshortage-accountants-we-should-be-worried-recruit-young-talent-2023-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eendangered%20species%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20that's%20endangering%20the%20financial%20ecosystem.%20But%20bolstering%20their%20ranks%20is%20no%20easy%20feat.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20pay%20is%20crappy%2C%20the%20hours%20are%20long%2C%20and%20the%20work%20is%20drudgery%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Richard%20Rampell%2C%20a%20retired%20accountant%20in%20South%20Florida.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20the%20drudgery%20is%20especially%20so%20in%20their%20early%20years.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECan%20America's%20most%20boring%20profession%20get%20sexier%2C%20stat%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20archetypal%20accountant%2C%20the%20dull%20quant%20wasting%20away%20in%20a%20cubicle%2C%20is%20far%20from%20a%20fantasy.%20Though%20CPAs%20can%20do%20plenty%20with%20their%20skills%20%E2%80%94%20forensic%20accountants%20working%20at%20the%20FBI%2C%20auditors%20helping%20a%20Fortune%20500%20company%20analyze%20the%20books%20of%20a%20hotshot%20business%20it's%20considering%20acquiring%20%E2%80%94%20the%20stereotype%20seems%20unshakable.%20Even%20the%20American%20Institute%20of%20CPAs%20has%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fyoutu.be%2FGnwz_qotLJQ%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Evideo%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20titled%20%26quot%3BAccounting%3A%20It's%20not%20what%20you%20think.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20always%20joke%20that%20nobody%20dreams%20of%20being%20an%20accountant%20when%20they're%20in%20the%20sandbox%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Amal%20Shehata%2C%20an%20accounting%20professor%20at%20New%20York%20University's%20Stern%20School%20of%20Business%20who%20worked%20at%20PricewaterhouseCoopers%20for%2010%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20stereotypes%20exist%20for%20a%20reason.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20hard%20to%20put%20lipstick%20on%20a%20pig%2C%26quot%3B%20Rampell%20said.%20He%20started%20his%20career%20at%20Ernst%20%26amp%3B%20Young%20(EY)%20in%20the%20late%201970s%2C%20then%20ran%20his%20own%20CPA%20firm%20in%20West%20Palm%20Beach%20for%2045%20years.%20%26quot%3BThe%20truth%20is%20that%20there's%20not%20a%20lot%20of%20glamour%20in%20accounting%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BYou%20can%20go%20out%20and%20have%20good%2C%20interesting%20clients%2C%20but%20that%20can%20take%20five%20or%2010%20years%20to%20know%20enough%20to%20get%20to%20that%20point.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccounting%20was%20never%20sexy%2C%20per%20se.%20But%20young%20people%20have%20never%20been%20more%20put%20off%20by%20unsexy%20careers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20job%20used%20to%20be%20as%20good%20as%20the%20long-term%20security%20it%20could%20guarantee.%20But%20now%2C%20many%20Gen%20Zers%20are%20hesitant%20to%20pursue%20jobs%20their%20peers%20consider%20overly%20safe%20or%20predictable.%20%26quot%3BI%20think%20there%20was%20a%20greater%20appeal%20to%20the%20industry%20in%20a%20previous%20era%2C%20when%20certainty%20and%20maintaining%20a%20job%20at%20one%20place%20for%20your%20entire%20career%20was%20seen%20as%20the%20ultimate%20goal%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Bryan%2C%20who's%2023.%20%26quot%3BNow%20it's%20not.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20recent%20survey%20by%20Deloitte%2C%2086%25%20of%20Gen%20Z%20respondents%20said%20that%20having%20a%20sense%20of%20purpose%20was%20important%20to%20their%20overall%20job%20satisfaction%20and%20well-being.%20Deloitte's%20report%20also%20describes%20them%20as%20%26quot%3Bincreasingly%20willing%20to%20reject%20assignments%20or%20employers%20who%20don't%20align%20with%20their%20values.%26quot%3B%20(Deloitte%20is%20also%20a%20Big%20Four%20accounting%20firm%2C%20along%20with%20EY%2C%20KPMG%2C%20and%20PwC.%20The%20company%20declined%20a%20request%20from%20Business%20Insider%20to%20discuss%20its%20efforts%20to%20counter%20the%20accountant%20shortage.)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGen%20Z%20is%20also%2C%20notably%2C%20the%20first%20generation%20to%20have%20truly%20grown%20up%20with%20social%20media.%20They%20spent%20their%20childhoods%20watching%20a%20stream%20of%20what%20everyone%20else%20does%20with%20their%20lives%2C%20and%20many%20have%20become%20convinced%20that%20that's%20much%20better%20than%20whatever%20they're%20doing%20with%20their%20own.%20In%20this%20way%2C%20social%20media%20has%20incentivized%20them%20to%20focus%20on%20doing%20things%20their%20peers%20deem%20interesting%20or%20exciting.%20And%2C%20well%2C%20accounting%20isn't%20readily%20Instagrammable.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThen%20there's%20the%20double-whammy%20problem%20of%20becoming%20an%20accountant%2C%20which%20is%20both%20harder%20to%20achieve%20and%20pays%20less%20than%20other%20finance%20jobs.%20A%20CPA%20candidate%20usually%20needs%20to%20get%20a%20master's%20in%20accounting%20to%20satisfy%20the%20requirement%20that%20they%20take%20150%20credit%20hours.%20After%20that%20comes%20the%20CPA%20exam%3A%20four%20grueling%20four-hour%20tests%20that%20must%20be%20passed%20within%2018%20months.%20And%20before%20they%20can%20officially%20get%20the%20title%2C%20candidates%20need%20to%20spend%20a%20year%20working%20under%20a%20licensed%20CPA.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBryan%20finished%20his%20graduate%20program%20in%20May%20and%20is%20set%20to%20begin%20his%20first%20job%20as%20an%20audit%20associate%20at%20a%20Big%20Four%20accounting%20firm%20in%20October.%20He's%20taken%20one%20of%20the%20CPA%20tests%2C%20which%20he%20described%20as%20%26quot%3Bbeastly%2C%26quot%3B%20and%20he%20spends%20most%20of%20his%20free%20time%20studying%20for%20the%20other%20three.%20%26quot%3BI%20think%20that%20it's%20necessary%2C%20but%20at%20the%20same%20time%2C%20it%20is%20definitely%20a%20substantial%20burden%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStudents%20can%20get%20higher-paying%20and%20arguably%20more%20exciting%20finance%20jobs%20right%20out%20of%20college%20without%20doing%20all%20that.%20That's%20what%20Bryan%20almost%20did.%20After%20a%20particularly%20tormenting%20high-school%20calculus%20class%20crushed%20his%20astrophysicist%20dreams%2C%20he%20considered%20pursuing%20investment%20banking.%20Most%20of%20his%20friends%20and%20classmates%20were%20going%20into%20finance%2C%20he%20said.%20And%20it's%20no%20wonder%20why.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEntry-level%20investment%20bankers%20can%20make%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Finvestment-bank-analyst-associate-starting-salaries-goldman-sachs-jpmorgan-citi-morgan-stanley%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Emore%20than%20%24100%2C000%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20base%20salary%20plus%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-bankers-spending-bonuses-yachts-porsches-real-estate-luxury-goods-2022-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eannual%20bonuses%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20the%20tens%20of%20thousands%20their%20first%20year%20out%20of%20undergrad.%20Bryan%20says%20he'll%20make%20%2472%2C000%20in%20his%20first%20year%20at%20his%20firm%20%E2%80%94%20one%20of%20the%20largest%2C%20most%20prestigious%2C%20and%20best-paid%20public%20accounting%20firms.Though%20junior%20investment%20bankers%20tend%20to%20work%20heinous%20hours%20and%20toil%20over%20pitch%20books%2C%20the%20field%20is%20widely%20seen%20as%20more%20posh.%20Bankers%20get%20to%20work%20on%20deal%20teams%20that%20advise%20the%20world's%20top%20executives%20on%20market-moving%20mergers%20and%20IPOs.%20They%20also%20tend%20to%20have%20direct%20access%20to%20other%20fancy%20Wall%20Street%20jobs%20at%20hedge%20funds%20and%20private-equity%20firms.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EEveryone%20I%20talked%20to%20agreed%20that%20the%20first%20thing%20to%20do%20to%20get%20more%20accountants%20is%20to%20pay%20them%20more.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BRaise%20the%20pay%20a%20lot%2C%20pay%20as%20much%20as%20the%20investment-banking%20firms%2C%26quot%3B%20Rampell%20said.%20%26quot%3BSo%20as%20long%20as%20there's%20demand%20for%20accounting%20services%2C%20tax%20preparation%2C%20auditing%2C%20and%20financial-statement%20preparation%2C%20there%20will%20be%20people%20that%20will%20rise%20to%20do%20that%20work.%20The%20firms%20will%20have%20to%20pay%20to%20meet%20the%20demand.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERampell%20worries%20that%20if%20salaries%20don't%20go%20up%2C%20the%20shortage%20could%20become%20a%20%26quot%3Bvicious%20cycle%26quot%3B%3A%20Fewer%20accountants%20means%20those%20who%20are%20around%20have%20larger%20workloads%2C%20and%20those%20people%20are%20more%20likely%20to%20quit%20because%20of%20the%20long%20hours%20and%20low%20pay.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20someone%20who%20ran%20a%20CPA%20firm%20for%20decades%2C%20Rampell%20said%20that%20paying%20employees%20more%20than%20his%20competitors%20was%20worth%20the%20cost.%20%26quot%3BI%20got%20more%20productive%20people%2C%20I%20got%20smarter%20people%2C%20I%20got%20harder-working%20people%20%E2%80%94%20people%20that%20were%20more%20ambitious%20and%20wanted%20to%20go%20places%20as%20opposed%20to%20people%20that%20just%20wanted%20work%209%20to%205.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20some%20signs%20that%20some%20firms%20are%20responding%20to%20calls%20for%20salary%20changes.%20Margaret%20Burke%2C%20the%20talent%20acquisition%20and%20development%20leader%20at%20PwC%2C%20said%20in%20a%20written%20statement%20that%20the%20firm%20has%20increased%20entry-level%20salaries%20for%20audit%20and%20tax%20associates%20%26quot%3Bover%20the%20last%20several%20years%2C%26quot%3B%20but%20declined%20to%20say%20by%20how%20much.%20She%20also%20pointed%20out%20that%20PwC%20gives%20performance-based%20raises%20and%20bonuses%20%26quot%3Bat%20all%20levels.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShehata%2C%20of%20NYU%2C%20said%20she%20also%20hopes%20alumni%20at%20top%20firms%20will%20help%20provide%20scholarships%20to%20make%20the%20cost%20of%20an%20extra%20year%20in%20grad%20school%20less%20exclusionary.%20%26quot%3BAs%20academic%20director%2C%20one%20of%20my%20priorities%20is%20really%20trying%20to%20find%20funding%20for%20the%20students%20who%20want%20to%20do%20the%20master's%20degree%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BThe%20expense%20can%20be%20prohibitive.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20way%20accounting%20is%20taught%20could%20also%20help%20stanch%20the%20shortage%2C%20Shehata%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20up%20to%20us%20as%20academics%20to%20make%20the%20curriculum%20exciting%20and%20interesting%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BTo%20me%2C%20that%20means%20it's%20relevant%20and%20it's%20timely.%26quot%3B%20For%20example%2C%20she%20recently%20taught%20a%20class%20about%20the%20intersection%20of%20the%20blockchain%20and%20accounting.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhat%20I%20try%20to%20encourage%20students%20to%20consider%20is%20the%20long%20game%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20added.%20%26quot%3BYes%2C%20there%20are%20hoops%20and%20obstacles%20and%20expenses%20to%20getting%20the%20credentials%2C%20but%20ultimately%20it%20pays%20off.%20It's%20not%20always%20the%20first%20job%3B%20it's%20later%20in%20life%20that%20those%20credentials%20and%20those%20skills%20can%20really%20pay%20off%20and%20benefit.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20said%20that's%20particularly%20true%20for%20those%20students%20who%20aren't%20sure%20what%20they%20want%20to%20do%20in%20the%20long%20term%2C%20because%20accounting%20is%20a%20skill%20you%20can%20draw%20upon%20in%20many%20types%20of%20industries.%20Shehata%20said%20some%20of%20her%20former%20accounting%20students%2C%20for%20example%2C%20were%20at%20places%20like%20Google%20and%20Apple%20in%20fraud%20detection.%20%26quot%3BAccounting%20is%20everywhere%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPerhaps%20the%20most%20important%20class%20to%20improve%20is%20the%20first%20one%20students%20take%2C%20Principles%20of%20Accounting.%20In%20May%2C%20the%20National%20Pipeline%20Advisory%20Group%20published%20an%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Faboutblaw.com%2Fbd3J%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20%3Cu%3E88-page%20report%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20%26quot%3Btalent%20solutions%26quot%3B%20for%20the%20field%2C%20which%20included%20reworking%20the%20intro%20course%2C%20given%20its%20%26quot%3Bpotential%20to%20shape%20a%20student's%20perception%20and%20ignite%20interest%20in%20an%20accounting%20career.%26quot%3B%20Bryan%20described%20this%20introduction%20as%20critical.%20The%20101%20classes%20%26quot%3Bdon't%20really%20do%20very%20much%20to%20convince%20you%20that%20accounting%20is%20more%20than%20bookkeeping%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BI%20think%20that%20if%20you%20were%20to%20change%20the%20way%20that%20those%20courses%20are%20taught%20to%20make%20it%20more%20applicable%20and%20less%20'Here's%20how%20to%20do%20this%20transaction%2C'%20I%20think%20you'd%20do%20a%20pretty%20good%20job%20of%20dismissing%20people%20of%20that%20notion.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20report's%20suggestions%20included%20%26quot%3Bplacing%20highly%20engaging%20instructors%26quot%3B%20in%20those%20classes%2C%20%26quot%3Bincorporating%20gamification%20and%20other%20technology%26quot%3B%20to%20%26quot%3Bstoke%20engagement%20and%20demonstrate%20the%20vital%20role%20technology%20plays%20in%20the%20accounting%20profession%2C%26quot%3B%20and%20exposing%20students%20to%20%26quot%3Bmore%20real-life%20accounting%20practitioners%20in%20a%20range%20of%20career%20vocations.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20report%20underscored%20another%20way%20to%20bolster%20accountants'%20ranks%3A%20make%20it%20easier%20to%20become%20one.%20It%20recommended%20easing%20the%20150-credit-hours%20requirement%20by%20%26quot%3Bmeasuring%20competency%20versus%20just%20academic%20experience%26quot%3B%20through%20%26quot%3Bexperiential%20learning%20that%20earns%20college%20credit%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20that%20is%2C%20less%20time%20in%20the%20classroom.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20firms%20have%20piloted%20similar%20models.%20EY%20has%20a%20Career%20Path%20Accelerator%20program%2C%20essentially%20an%20alternative%20to%20a%20master's-degree%20requirement%2C%20and%20Burke%2C%20of%20PwC%2C%20pointed%20to%20its%20work-for-credit%20program%20at%20Saint%20Peter's%20University.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERampell%20thinks%20that%20while%20supply%20and%20demand%20will%20naturally%20work%20itself%20out%2C%20in%20the%20meantime%2C%20%26quot%3Bthere'll%20be%20a%20lot%20of%20pain.%26quot%3B%20The%20shortage%2C%20he%20added%2C%20is%20%26quot%3Bsort%20of%20like%20when%20you%20want%20to%20find%20a%20doctor%20but%20you%20can't%20make%20an%20appointment%20for%20three%20months%20because%20they're%20so%20busy.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShehata%20said%20a%20shortage%20costs%20companies%20themselves%20and%20the%20investors%20who%20put%20their%20trust%20and%20money%20into%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20you're%20running%20a%20business%2C%20you%20need%20to%20be%20able%20to%20make%20educated%2C%20informed%20decisions.%20How%20do%20you%20make%20informed%20decisions%20if%20you%20don't%20have%20the%20accounting%20data%3F%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BWe%20want%20to%20make%20sure%20that%20we%20have%20trust%20in%20our%20capital-market%20system.%20People%20make%20decisions%20based%20on%20financial%20reporting%20%E2%80%94%20there%20are%20people's%20livelihoods%20and%20investments%20in%20that.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fauthor%2Femmalyse-brownstein%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EEmmalyse%20Brownstein%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20is%20a%20reporter%20on%20Business%20Insider's%20finance%20team.%20Her%20coverage%20is%20focused%20on%20Wall%20Street%20culture%20and%20careers.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Faccountant-shortage-sexy-taxes-business-school-pwc-kpmg-2024-8%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1724666282000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66c8da5143b5e59d16b4cc7a%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Faccountant-shortage-sexy-taxes-business-school-pwc-kpmg-2024-8%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Inside%20the%20desperate%20campaign%20to%20get%20Gen%20Z%20to%20become%20accountants%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22ebrownstein%40businessinsider.com%20(Emmalyse%20Brownstein)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A54%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Faccountant-shortage-sexy-taxes-business-school-pwc-kpmg-2024-8%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Youjoung%20and%20Lee%20Kyu%20Han%20end%20romance%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1724666264000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-112804581%2Cimgsize-138616.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fweb-series%2Fnews%2Fkorean%2Fyouj