%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EBut%20the%20company%20is%20not%20infallible%2C%20as%20it%20bleeds%20cash%20and%20rival%20companies%20catch%20up.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EIndustry%20experts%20told%20BI%20how%20OpenAI%20could%20maintain%20its%20lead%20and%20how%20AGI%20comes%20into%20play.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchatgpt-on-track-to-set-new-record-for-web-traffic-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EOpenAI%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20the%20buzziest%20company%20in%20the%20field%20of%20AI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWithin%20two%20months%20of%20launching%20ChatGPT%20in%202022%2C%20the%20chatbot%20had%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchatgpt-may-be-fastest-growing-app-in-history-ubs-study-2023-2%23%3A~%3Atext%3DChatGPT%2520may%2520be%2520the%2520fastest%252Dgrowing%2520app%2520in%2520history%2520with%2Ceasy%2520access%2520and%2520faster%2520responses.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eaccrued%20some%20100%20million%20monthly%20users%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20setting%20the%20record%20for%20the%20fastest-growing%20user%20base%20of%20any%20consumer%20application%20in%20history.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20company%20also%20tripled%20its%20valuation%20to%20over%20%2480%20billion%20in%20the%20last%20year%2C%20thanks%20in%20part%20to%20investments%20from%20tech%20giants%20like%20Microsoft%2C%20which%20has%20funneled%20some%20%2413%20billion%20into%20it.%20Apple%20is%20integrating%20ChatGPT%20into%20its%20leading%20products.%20And%20the%20company%20is%20now%20gearing%20up%20to%20launch%20its%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fopenai-gpt5-gpt4-expectations-ai-2024-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emost%20advanced%20model%20yet%2C%20GPT-5%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EArmed%20with%20a%20roster%20of%20top%20talent%20and%20over%20%2411%20billion%20in%20support%20from%20investors%20outside%20Microsoft%2C%20OpenAI%20has%20comfortably%20positioned%20itself%20ahead%20of%20its%20competitors.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20company%20is%20not%20infallible.%20Altman's%20recent%20projections%20show%20that%20the%20company%20will%20hit%20%243.4%20billion%20in%20annual%20revenue%20this%20year%20but%20incur%20at%20least%20%245%20billion%20in%20losses.%20Those%20losses%20and%20a%20lack%20of%20any%20clear%20path%20to%20profitability%20in%20the%20near%20future%20are%20beginning%20to%20make%20investors%20nervous.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInvestor%20anxiety%20exists%20around%20other%20Big%20Tech%20companies%2C%20too%2C%20like%20Meta%2C%20Google%2C%20Apple%2C%20Amazon%2C%20and%20Microsoft.%20Huge%20spending%20on%20AI%20coupled%20with%20disappointing%20earnings%20contributed%20to%20a%20sell-off%20in%20the%20tech%20industry%20earlier%20this%20month.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%2C%20how%20much%20runway%20will%20investors%20be%20willing%20to%20give%20OpenAI%20before%20it%20can%20start%20making%20money%3F%20Is%20OpenAI%20too%20dominant%20for%20investors%20to%20give%20up%20on%3F%20We%20asked%20the%20experts.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%229b044ab1-4a89-4cb8-893d-1038a62661c7%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EOpenAI%20needs%20to%20retain%20its%20talent%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EInvestors%20are%20pouring%20money%20into%20OpenAI%20in%20part%20because%20it's%20an%20incubator%20of%20some%20of%20the%20brightest%20minds%20in%20the%20AI%20industry%20%E2%80%94%20so%20retaining%20them%20is%20key%20to%20keeping%20its%20backers%20happy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOpenAI%20first%20launched%20in%202015%20as%20a%20nonprofit%20dedicated%20to%20developing%20artificial%20general%20intelligence%20%E2%80%94%20a%20theoretical%20future%20AI%20that%20can%20reason%20like%20humans%20%E2%80%94%20that%20is%20%26quot%3Bmost%20likely%20to%20benefit%20humanity%20as%20a%20whole.%26quot%3B%20But%20the%20company%20also%20added%20a%20for-profit%20arm%20in%202019%20to%20fund%20its%20capital-intensive%20mission.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20move%20led%20to%20some%20disagreements%20between%20its%20aggressive%20profit-driven%20faction%20and%20the%20more%20cautious%2C%20safety-conscious%20side.%20It%20came%20to%20a%20head%20last%20year%20when%20the%20OpenAI%20board%20briefly%2C%20yet%20unsuccessfully%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhat-sam-altman-did-so-bad-he-got-fired-openai-2023-12%23%3A~%3Atext%3DNew%2520reports%2520suggest%2520Altman%2520may%2Cmaintain%2520power%252C%2520the%2520reports%2520say.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eousted%20CEO%20Sam%20Altman%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAltman%20was%20saved%2C%20in%20part%2C%20by%20public%20support%20from%20OpenAI's%20employees.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20company%20has%20lured%20some%20of%20the%20AI%20industry's%20most%20talented%20minds%20over%20the%20years%2C%20sometimes%20aggressively%20poaching%20employees%20from%20its%20competitors%2C%20including%20Google.%20An%20analysis%20by%20BI%20found%20that%20at%20least%2044%20ex-Googlers%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fopenai-google-poaching-staff-ai-talent-war-sam-altman-2024-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ejumped%20ship%20to%20OpenAI%3C%2Fa%3E%20since%20the%20beginning%20of%20the%20year%20alone.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Information%2C%20a%20tech%20publication%2C%20reported%20that%20OpenAI%20is%20set%20to%20spend%20%248%20billion%20in%202024%2C%20with%20at%20least%20%241.5%20billion%20going%20into%20hiring%20talent.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAjay%20Agrawal%2C%20a%20professor%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Toronto%20who%20co-authored%20a%20book%20on%20the%20economics%20of%20AI%2C%20told%20BI%20that%20hiring%20the%20world's%20best%20engineers%20and%20researchers%20is%20part%20of%20OpenAI's%20edge%20and%20the%20cash%20burn%20is%20strategically%20sound%20in%20a%20still%20nascent%20market.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20would%20say%20that%20their%20strategy%2C%20which%20is%20making%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Every%20large%20investments%20than%20their%20current%20revenues%20can%20support%2C%20seems%20to%20make%20a%20lot%20of%20sense%20because%20they're%20competing%20in%20a%20market%20that%20is%20new%2C%26quot%3B%20Agrawal%20said%2C%20adding%20that%20the%20potential%20size%20of%20the%20AI%20market%20is%20still%20unknown.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInvestors%20and%20partners%20will%20likely%20be%20empathetic%20toward%20OpenAI's%20capital%20needs%20to%20maintain%20talent%2C%20Mahdi%20Raza%2C%20cofounder%20and%20a%20managing%20partner%20of%20Exponent%20Founders%20Capital%2C%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BInvestors%20will%20continue%20to%20be%20excited%20to%20fund%20OpenAI%20as%20long%20as%20they%20continue%20to%20accrue%20a%20compounding%20customer%2C%20compute%2C%20and%20talent%20advantage%2C%26quot%3B%20Raza%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20to%20retain%20that%20talent%2C%20the%20company%20must%20maintain%20the%20culture%20and%20mission%20that%20first%20attracted%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAs%20they%20become%20more%20commercial%2C%20partner%20more%20with%20companies%20like%20Microsoft%20and%20Apple%2C%20and%20as%20their%20valuation%20goes%20up%2C%20there's%20real%20risk%20that%20the%20culture%20changes%2C%26quot%3B%20Brad%20Porter%2C%20the%20CEO%20of%20robotics%20company%20Collaborative%20Robots%2C%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESeveral%20high-profile%20researchers%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fopenai-brain-drain-isnt-great-for-sam-altman-competition-2024-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehave%20already%20left%20the%20company%3C%2Fa%3E.%20OpenAI's%20former%20chief%20scientist%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Filya-sutskever-leaving-openai-6-months-after-failed-altman-ouster-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EIlya%20Sutskever%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20left%20in%20May%20because%20he%20didn't%20agree%20with%20Altman's%20aggressive%20approach%20to%20rolling%20out%20new%20products.%20He's%20since%20launched%20his%20own%20venture%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fman-who-revolted-against-sam-altman-just-started-research-lab-2024-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESafe%20Superintelligence%20Inc.%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20bills%20itself%20as%20taking%20a%20more%20responsible%20approach%20to%20AI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJan%20Leike%2C%20who%20helped%20lead%20OpeanAI's%20superalignment%20team%2C%20which%20worked%20to%20ensure%20that%20the%20company's%20AI%20technology%20was%20safe%20for%20human%20society%2C%20also%20jumped%20to%20its%20rival%20Anthropic.%20Its%20cofounder%2C%20John%20Schulman%2C%20announced%20recently%20he%2C%20too%2C%20was%20leaving%20for%20Anthropic.%20Researchers%20Daniel%20Kokotajlo%20and%20William%20Saunders%20also%20departed%20earlier%20this%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAnyone%20at%20OpenAI%20can%20start%20their%20own%20company%20now%20or%20join%20another%2C%20so%20their%20position%20is%20more%20precarious%20than%20ever%2C%26quot%3B%20Porter%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%2C%20whether%20top%20researchers%20stay%20%E2%80%94%20or%20go%20%E2%80%94%20might%20be%20the%20clearest%20test%20of%20the%20company's%20strength.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%2C%20internally%2C%20they%20continue%20to%20know%20they%20have%20the%20best%20AI%20and%20truly%20feel%20that%20they%20are%20the%20closest%20to%20realizing%20the%20vision%20of%20AGI%2C%20then%20most%20will%20want%20to%20stay%20to%20see%20that%20vision%20come%20to%20life%2C%26quot%3B%20Porter%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2244f7f591-1014-422b-8e0a-99a3cedb09de%5C%22%3EOpenAI's%20first-mover%20advantage%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EBecause%20of%20OpenAI's%20aggressive%20investments%2C%20the%20company's%20technology%20is%20often%20seen%20as%20the%20gold%20standard%20for%20large%20language%20models.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20it%20has%20competition.%20And%20that%20could%20cause%20investors%20to%20start%20looking%20elsewhere%2C%20experts%20told%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BGiven%20the%20velocity%20of%20new%20development%2C%20it%20would%20not%20be%20unforeseen%20for%20more%20nimble%20competitors%20to%20spring%20up%20and%20some%20of%20the%20Big%20Tech%20AI%20incumbents%20to%20encroach%20and%20threaten%20their%20business%2C%26quot%3B%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3ENicos%20Vekiarides%2C%20the%20founder%20and%20CEO%20of%20digital%20media%20validation%20company%20Attestiv%2C%20told%20BI%20in%20a%20written%20note.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMark%20Zuckerberg's%20Meta%20released%20its%20latest%20iteration%20of%20the%20Llama%20model%20in%20July.%20Google%20launched%20Gemini%20last%20year%2C%20and%20Microsoft%2C%20an%20OpenAI%20partner%2C%20recently%20identified%20the%20ChatGPT-maker%20as%20a%20competitor.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOpenAI's%20models%20are%20industry-leading%2C%20but%20companies%20know%20they%20have%20other%20options%2C%20Agrawal%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20think%20there's%20an%20increasing%20dependence%20on%20OpenAI%20models.%20I%20think%20their%20competitors%20are%20trying%20to%20reduce%20the%20dependence%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%2C%20pointing%20to%20Microsoft%20as%20an%20example.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20recent%20SEC%20filing%2C%20Microsoft%20acknowledged%20the%20%26quot%3Blong-term%20partnership%26quot%3B%20with%20OpenAI%20but%20also%20called%20the%20company%20its%20competitor.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOur%20AI%20offerings%20compete%20with%20AI%20products%20from%20hyperscalers%20such%20as%20Amazon%20and%20Google%2C%20as%20well%20as%20products%20from%20other%20emerging%20competitors%2C%20including%20Anthropic%2C%20OpenAI%2C%20Meta%2C%20and%20other%20open%20source%20offerings%2C%20many%20of%20which%20are%20also%20current%20or%20potential%20partners%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20company%20wrote%20in%20the%20filing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAgrawal%20added%20that%20few%20corporations%2C%20if%20any%2C%20have%20%26quot%3Bextremely%20high%20dependencies%26quot%3B%20on%20OpenAI%20that%20would%20prevent%20the%20use%20of%20substitute%20models.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERaza%20agreed%2C%20noting%20that%20it's%20also%20unclear%20whether%20OpenAI's%20models%20exhibit%20a%20real%20technical%20defensibility%20against%20competitors.%20%26quot%3BAny%20model%20advantage%20so%20far%2