A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fentertainment%2Fhindi%2Fbollywood%2Fnews%2Fshraddha-kapoor-down-with-viral-fever-exclusive%2Farticleshow%2F112801446.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Opinion%3A%20Kamala%20Harris%2C%20Sunak%2C%20Obama%2C%20And%20Their%20Struggle%20To%20Truly%20'Belong'%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3Cimg%20alt%3D%5C%22Latest%20and%20Breaking%20News%20on%20NDTV%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Latest%20and%20Breaking%20News%20on%20NDTV%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-08%2F3d47t378_kamala-harris_625x300_26_August_24.jpg%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20Democratic%20National%20Convention%20(DNC)%20stage%20in%20Chicago%2C%20Little%20Amara%20shouts%2C%20%26quot%3BEverybody%20over%20here%2C%20say%20'Kama'.%26quot%3B%20Then%20joins%20in%20her%20sister%2C%20Leela%2C%20%26quot%3BEverybody%20over%20here%2C%20say%20'La'.%26quot%3B%20The%20lesson%20continues%2C%20%26quot%3BTogether%20'Kama-la.'%26quot%3B%20The%20excited%20crowd%20shouts%20in%20unison%2C%20%3Cem%3E%26quot%3BKaama-la%26quot%3B%3C%2Fem%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20two%20young%20women%20are%20the%20grand-nieces%20of%20the%20US%20Vice-President%20and%20the%20Democratic%20Party's%20presidential%20candidate%2C%20Kamala%20Harris.%20It's%20ironic%20that%20a%20nation%20that%20has%20seen%20its%20Vice%20President%20work%20tirelessly%20for%20the%20past%20three-and-a-half%20years%20still%20needs%20a%20lesson%20in%20pronouncing%20her%20first%20name.%20Even%20then%2C%20they%20don't%20get%20it%20right.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20pronunciation%20of%20her%20name%20is%20just%20scratching%20the%20surface.%20Kamala%2C%20in%20essence%2C%20is%20yet%20another%20example%20of%20how%20across%20the%20West%2C%20even%20if%20political%20leaders%20of%20colour%20manage%20to%20reach%20the%20top%2C%20they%20find%20themselves%20operating%20within%20systems%20that%20remain%20resistant%20to%20profound%20transformation%20and%20dominated%20by%20White%20leaders.%20Behind%20their%20historic%20achievements%20still%20lies%20that%20complex%20web%20of%20said%20and%20unsaid%20racism%2C%20bias%2C%20and%20discrimination%2C%20which%20continues%20to%20affect%20politicians%20and%20celebrities%20of%20colour%2C%20even%20at%20the%20highest%20levels%20of%20power.%20Barack%20Obama%2C%20Rishi%20Sunak%2C%20and%20even%20leaders%20who%20deny%20this%20reality%2C%20like%20Nikki%20Haley%20and%20Priti%20Patel%2C%20have%20all%20had%20to%20contend%20with%20it.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EJustifying%20Her%20Name%2C%20And%20Also%20Her%20Place%20In%20America%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20DNC%2C%20after%20that%20elaborate%20pronunciation%20lesson%2C%20'Kaamala'%20-%20as%20the%20Americans%20pronounce%20it%20-%20went%20on%20to%20introduce%20herself%20to%20a%20nation%20she%20was%20born%20in%2059%20years%20ago.%20Daughter%20to%20immigrant%20parents%2C%20she%20tried%20to%20connect%20with%20her%20people%20emotionally.%20She%20spoke%20about%20herself%2C%20her%20beloved%20Indian%20mother%2C%20her%20sister%2C%20her%20Jamaican%20connection%20through%20her%20father%2C%20and%20her%20strong%20Indian%20links.%20The%20media%20was%20kind%20enough%20to%20say%20she%20%26quot%3Breintroduced%26quot%3B%20herself%20to%20all%20Americans.%20In%20her%2040-minute-long%20speech%2C%20she%20urged%20people%20of%20colour%20to%20%26quot%3Bnever%20let%20anyone%20tell%20you%20who%20you%20are.%20You%20show%20them%20who%20you%20are%26quot%3B.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnd%20yet%2C%20she%20dedicated%20her%20whole%20speech%20telling%20all%20Americans%20who%20she%20was.%20She%20had%20to.%20It%20was%20not%20enough%20for%20her%20country%20folks%20that%20in%202021%20she%20shattered%20all%20glass%20ceilings%20by%20becoming%20the%20first%20woman%2C%20first%20Black%20American%2C%20and%20first%20Indian%20American%20to%20hold%20the%20office%20of%20Vice-President%20of%20the%20United%20States.%20She%20passionately%20declared%20in%20Chicago%2C%20%26quot%3BI%20promise%20to%20be%20a%20President%20for%20all%20Americans.%26quot%3B%20And%2C%20as%20if%20unsure%20of%20the%20people's%20trust%20in%20her%2C%20Harris%20pleaded%20with%20the%20people%20to%20put%20faith%20in%20her%2C%20%26quot%3BYou%20can%20always%20trust%20me%20to%20put%20country%20above%20party%20and%20self.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EBiden%20Didn't%20Have%20To%20Re-Introduce%20Himself%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20difference%20between%20President%20Joe%20Biden%20and%20Kamala%20Harris%20is%20perhaps%20the%20fact%20that%20Biden%20was%20Obama's%20running%20mate%20twice%2C%20and%20both%20times%2C%20he%20did%20not%20have%20to%20get%20someone%20to%20tell%20the%20nation%20whether%20his%20name%20was%20pronounced%20as%20'Biden'%2C%20'Beden'%2C%20or%20'Byden'.%20He%20did%20not%20have%20to%20%26quot%3Bre-introduce%26quot%3B%20himself%2C%20and%20he%20did%20not%20have%20to%20punch%20above%20his%20weight.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThose%20privileges%20are%20not%20available%20to%20Kamala%20Harris.%C2%A0It%20has%20been%20a%20euphoric%20few%20days%20for%20Harris%2C%20and%20it's%20true%20that%20her%20party%20has%20welcomed%20her%20with%20open%20arms%2C%20and%20that%20she%20has%20so%20far%20been%20getting%20good%20press.%20But%20the%20question%20is%2C%20is%20America%20itself%20ready%20to%20accept%20a%20woman%20-%20and%20a%20person%20of%20colour%20-%20as%20President%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EObama%20Couldn't%20Escape%20Racism.%20Kamala%20Can't%20Either%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhen%20Barack%20Obama%20burst%20onto%20the%20political%20centre%20stage%2C%20campaigning%20for%20the%20coveted%20post%20in%202008%2C%20many%20had%20questioned%20whether%20America%20was%20ready%20for%20a%20Black%20President.%20He%20swept%20away%20the%20last%20racial%20barrier%20in%20American%20politics%20without%20much%20trouble.%20But%20even%20Obama%20faced%20questions%20about%20his%20birth%20certificate%20and%20legitimacy%2C%20something%20that%20has%20come%20to%20be%20known%20as%20the%20'birther%20conspiracy'.%20It's%20a%20false%20and%20racist%20theory%20that%20claims%20Obama%20was%20not%20born%20in%20the%20United%20States%20and%20was%20therefore%20ineligible%20to%20be%20president.%20The%20theory%20was%20heavily%20promoted%20by%20former%20President%20and%20now%20Harris's%20Republican%20opponent%20Donald%20Trump%2C%20who%20was%20a%20private%20citizen%20at%20the%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhen%20he%20was%20finally%20elected%2C%20Obama%20offered%20hope%20and%20promised%20change-something%20Harris%20is%20repackaging%20today.%20But%20Trump%2C%20too%2C%20is%20repackaging%20his%20old%20playbook.%20He%20recently%20questioned%20Harris's%20racial%20identity%20in%20Chicago%20during%20a%20heated%20exchange%20at%20a%20convention%20for%20Black%20journalists%3B%20he%20had%20earlier%20even%20insinuated%20that%20Harris%20was%20%26quot%3Bnot%20American%20enough%26quot%3B%20to%20be%20the%20President.%20Kamala%20herself%20has%20spoken%20publicly%20about%20her%20experiences%20with%20racism%20and%20discrimination.%20In%20her%20memoir%20The%20Truths%20We%20Hold%2C%20she%20wrote%20about%20her%20mother%2C%20Shyamala%20Gopalan%2C%20teaching%20her%20and%20her%20sister%20how%20to%20cope%20with%20racism%3A%20%26quot%3BMy%20mother%20would%20say%2C%20'You%20will%20be%20faced%20with%20people%20who%20don't%20like%20you%20because%20of%20the%20colour%20of%20your%20skin.%20But%20you%20must%20never%20let%20that%20define%20you.'%26quot%3B%20In%20a%202020%20speech%2C%20she%20spoke%20about%20the%20challenges%20of%20overcoming%20stereotypes%3A%20%26quot%3BAs%20a%20woman%20of%20colour%2C%20I've%20had%20to%20fight%20to%20be%20seen%2C%20to%20be%20heard%2C%20and%20to%20be%20believed...%20But%20I've%20never%20let%20anyone%20define%20me%20or%20my%20potential.%26quot%3B%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ESunak's%20Story%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20problem%20non-White%20politicians%20face%20is%20universal%20across%20the%20West.%20During%20the%20UK%20election%20campaign%20early%20last%20month%2C%20a%20leader%20of%20Nigel%20Farage's%20Reform%20Party%20passed%20racist%20comments%20against%20his%20own%20sitting%20Prime%20Minister%2C%20calling%20Sunak%20a%20%26quot%3BPaki%26quot%3B.%20Sunak%20was%20angry%2C%20but%20he%20did%20not%20push%20back%20enough%20except%20to%20show%20his%20hurt%20during%20a%20media%20interview%3A%20%26quot%3BMy%20two%20daughters%20have%20to%20see%20and%20hear%20Reform%20people%20who%20campaign%20for%20Nigel%20Farage%20calling%20me%20an%20'effing%20P***'.%20It%20hurts%2C%20and%20it%20makes%20me%20angry%2C%20and%20I%20think%20he%20has%20some%20questions%20to%20answer.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20was%20jubilation%20all%20over%20the%20UK%20when%20Rishi%20Sunak%20became%20the%20Prime%20Minister%20in%202022.%20From%20relative%20obscurity%20in%202015%2C%20when%20he%20was%20elected%20as%20an%20MP%20for%20the%20first%20time%2C%20to%20becoming%20the%20country's%20first%20Indian-origin%2C%20Hindu%20Prime%20Minister%2C%20Sunak's%20was%20a%20fairytale%20story.%20Back%20then%20I%20had%20been%20told%20by%20White%20people%2C%20Pakistani%20and%20Bangladesh-origin%20people%20that%20Rishi%20Sunak%20was%20the%20right%20choice.%20His%20leadership%20was%20lauded%20as%20evidence%20of%20the%20UK's%20commitment%20to%20diversity%20and%20meritocracy.%20But%20despite%20his%20position%2C%20Sunak%20was%20subjected%20to%20racial%20slurs%20and%20scepticism%20about%20his%20loyalty%20and%20cultural%20affiliations.%20Even%20the%20office%20of%20the%20Prime%20Minister%20could%20not%20exempt%20him%20from%20the%20prejudices%20and%20challenges%20faced%20by%20other%20people%20of%20colour.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20experiences%20of%20Obama%2C%20Kamala%2C%20and%20Sunak%2C%20along%20with%20other%20politicians%20of%20Indian%20descent%2C%20such%20as%20Priti%20Patel%20in%20the%20UK%20or%20Nikki%20Haley%20in%20the%20US%2C%20illustrate%20a%20broader%20pattern%20where%20the%20representation%20of%20minority%20groups%20in%20politics%20is%20no%20doubt%20celebrated%20but%20does%20not%20necessarily%20translate%20into%20meaningful%20change%20for%20those%20communities.%20The%20control%2C%20decision-making%20powers%20and%20authority%20remain%20with%20the%20White%20masters%20-%20even%20if%20leaders%20like%20Patel%20and%20Haley%20continue%20to%20defend%20racist%20and%20discriminatory%20actions%20or%20remarks%20against%20the%20people%20of%20their%20communities.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20Battle%20Ahead%20For%20Kamala%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnyway%2C%20it%20has%20been%20smooth%20sailing%20for%20Kamala%20Harris%20so%20far.%20But%20she%20faces%20an%20opponent%20known%20for%20dealing%20in%20personal%20insults.%20Apparently%2C%20Trump%20knew%20before%20Joe%20Biden%20withdrew%20himself%20from%20the%20race%20that%20he%20would%20be%20replaced%20by%20Harris.%20He%20told%20a%20crowd%20about%20it%20much%20before%20her%20nomination%2C%20%26quot%3BI%20got%20him%20%5BJoe%20Biden%5D%20out%20of%20the%20race%2C%20and%20that%20means%20we%20have%20Kamala.%26quot%3B%20Trump%20then%20added%2C%20%26quot%3BShe's%20so%20bad.%20She's%20so%20pathetic.%26quot%3B%20He%20has%20already%20questioned%20her%20racial%20identity%2C%20and%20is%20now%20on%20to%20find%20a%20nickname%20for%20her%20that%20sticks.%20%C2%A0His%20personal%20attacks%20continue%20as%20he%20keeps%20reminding%20his%20supporters%20that%20she%20laughs%20like%20a%20%26quot%3Blunatic%26quot%3B%20and%20is%20%26quot%3Bcrazy%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20Kamala%20Harris%2C%20after%20a%20fantastic%20first%20few%20weeks%2C%20the%20honeymoon%20will%20well%20and%20truly%20be%20over%20soon.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E(Syed%20Zubair%20Ahmed%20is%20a%20London-based%20senior%20Indian%20journalist%20with%20three%20decades%20of%20experience%20with%20the%20Western%20media)%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDisclaimer%3A%20These%20are%20the%20personal%20opinions%2